anies%20around%26quot%3B%20for%20any%20employee%20who%20doesn't%20wish%20to%20abide%20by%20the%20new%20policy%2C%20according%20to%20a%20transcript%20of%20the%20meeting%20reviewed%20by%20BI.%20He%20added%20that%20he%20didn't%20mean%20it%20in%20a%20%26quot%3Bbad%20way.%26quot%3B%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ESome%20employees%20aren't%20buying%20Garman's%20comments%20that%20most%20people%20he%20had%20spoken%20with%20were%20%26quot%3Bactually%20quite%20excited%20by%20this%20change%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20copy%20of%20the%20letter%20and%20internal%20Slack%20messages%20viewed%20by%20BI%20showed.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EThe%20letter%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BBy%20rigidly%20mandating%20a%205-day%20in-office%20culture%20and%20telling%20employees%20who%20cannot%20or%20will%20not%20contribute%20to%20the%20company's%20mission%20in%20this%20specific%20way%20that%20'there%20are%20other%20companies%20around%2C'%20you%20are%20silencing%20critical%20perspectives%20and%20damaging%20our%20culture%20and%20our%20future%20in%20doing%20so.%26quot%3B%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EGarman%20also%20said%20in%20the%20all-hands%20meeting%20that%20he%20hadn't%20seen%20people's%20ability%20to%20%26quot%3Breally%20innovate%26quot%3B%20when%20they're%20not%20working%20together%20in%20person.%20The%20letter%20said%20his%20comments%20did%20%26quot%3Bnot%20align%20with%20the%20experiences%20of%20many%20employees.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20messages%20viewed%20by%20BI%2C%20one%20staffer%20wrote%20on%20an%20Amazon%20Slack%20channel%3A%20%26quot%3BThis%20statement%20from%20Matt%20doesn't%20ring%20true%20with%20me%20or%20our%20teams.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20staffer%20said%20Garman%20%26quot%3Bambushed-%20er%20spontaneously%20approached%20random%20AWS%20engineers%26quot%3B%20at%20the%20company's%20headquarters%20to%20gather%20the%20consensus%20that%20most%20employees%20he'd%20talked%20to%20were%20excited%20by%20the%20RTO%20mandate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGarman's%20remarks%20came%20after%20Amazon%20said%20in%20September%20it%20would%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-rto-faq-document-spells-out-new-rule-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erequire%20employees%20to%20work%20from%20the%20office%3C%2Fa%3E%20every%20day%20beginning%20next%20year.%20The%20policy%20is%20stricter%20than%20at%20Amazon's%20peer%20companies%20and%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-workers-blast-strict-rto-mandate-five-days-week-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eby%20some%20accounts%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20stricter%20than%20Amazon's%20office-work%20policy%20before%20the%20pandemic.%20Amazon%20CEO%20Andy%20Jassy%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aboutamazon.com%2Fnews%2Fcompany-news%2Fceo-andy-jassy-latest-update-on-amazon-return-to-office-manager-team-ratio%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ein%20a%20memo%20announcing%20the%20mandate%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20said%20that%20the%20company%20had%20made%20the%20decision%20to%20%26quot%3Bfurther%20strengthen%26quot%3B%20its%20culture%20and%20teams.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmazon%20had%201.5%20million%20employees%20in%202023%2C%20most%20of%20whom%20worked%20in%20warehouses.%20There%20are%20more%20than%2030%2C000%20employees%20on%20the%20internal%20Slack%20channel%20where%20the%20letter%20originated.%20The%20letter%20has%20been%20signed%20by%20523%20staff%20from%20Amazon%20and%20AWS%2C%20with%20172%20of%20those%20including%20their%20names.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20response%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20about%20the%20letter%2C%20an%20Amazon%20spokesperson%2C%20Margaret%20Callahan%2C%20told%20BI%20the%20company%20was%20offering%20resources%20to%20employees%20depending%20on%20their%20location%2C%20including%20elder%20care%2C%20pet%20sitters%2C%20caregiver%20referral%20services%2C%20and%20commuter%20benefits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERead%20a%20full%20copy%20of%20the%20open%20letter%20below%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3EMr.%20Garman%2C%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cbr%3EAs%20employees%20of%20AWS%20and%20Amazon%20who%20work%20tirelessly%20every%20day%20to%20obsess%20over%20and%20innovate%20on%20behalf%20of%20our%20customers%2C%20we%20were%20appalled%20to%20hear%20the%20non-data-driven%20explanation%20you%20gave%20for%20Amazon%20imposing%20a%205-day%20in-office%20mandate%20at%20the%20AWS%20Global%20Meeting%20on%20October%2017th.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cbr%3EYour%20comments%2C%20in%20part%2C%20stated%3A%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3EI%20think%20nine%20out%20of%20ten%20people%20are%20actually%20quite%20excited%20by%20this%20change.%20There's%20a%20number%20of%20reasons%20for%20it%20...%20what%20makes%20Amazon%20special%20is%20our%20ability%20to%20debate%20and%20our%20ability%20to%20innovate.%20And%20when%20we%20want%20to%20innovate%2C%20when%20we%20want%20to%20really%2C%20really%20innovate%20on%20interesting%20products%2C%20I%20have%20not%20seen%20an%20ability%20for%20us%20to%20do%20that%20when%20we're%20not%20in-person.%20There%20is%20just%20no%20substitute%20for%20getting%20up%20on%20a%20whiteboard%20and%20walking%20through%20what's%20going%20on%2C%20having%20a%20brainstorm%20and%20stopping%20in%20the%20cubicle%20next%20to%20you%20and%20asking%20the%20person%20where%20it%20is%2C%20and%20grabbing%20coffee%20or%20lunch%20together%20and%20chatting%20about%20it%2C%20learning%20what%20other%20people%20are%20working%20on%20and%20it%20sparking%20something%20in%20what%20you're%20working%20on%20%E2%80%94%20that%20just%20doesn't%20work%20when%20you're%20working%20remote%2C%20it%20just%20doesn't%20happen%20...%20And%20so%20we%20feel%2C%20and%20I%20feel%20very%20strongly%20that%20that%20is%20just%20such%20an%20important%20part%20of%20the%20company%20that%20getting%20us%20back%20in%20the%20office%20and%20in%20an%20office%20setting%20is%20super%20important.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cbr%3ENot%20only%20are%20these%20comments%20inconsistent%20with%20the%20experiences%20of%20many%20employees%2C%20they%20indicate%20an%20outright%20abdication%20of%20AWS'%20role%20as%20one%20of%20the%20world's%20most%20innovative%20companies%20and%20a%20leader%20in%20our%20industry.%20By%20making%20these%20statements%2C%20you%20are%20continuing%20and%20compounding%20a%20trend%20by%20Amazon's%20S-team%20of%20misrepresenting%20the%20realities%20of%20working%20at%20Amazon%20and%20the%20impact%20this%20mandate%20will%20have%20on%20the%20company%20and%2C%20by%20extension%2C%20its%20customers.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cbr%3EAmazon%20claims%20to%20be%20a%20data-driven%20company%2C%20and%20statements%20which%20rely%20on%20%26quot%3Bwe%20believe%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BI%20feel%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20exclaim%20how%20many%20people%20are%20excited%20about%20something%20to%20justify%20themselves%20fail%20to%20achieve%20our%20standard%20of%20decision%20making%20for%20critical%20issues%20that%20impact%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20the%20company's%20employees%20and%20its%20customers.%20Your%20statements%20indicate%20that%20either%20you%20have%20not%20collected%20enough%20data%20to%20support%20your%20position%20but%20are%20moving%20ahead%20anyways%2C%20or%20you%20have%20seen%20the%20data%20which%20indicates%20otherwise%20and%20are%20choosing%20to%20ignore%20it%2C%20or%20you%20have%20motivations%20to%20support%20this%20policy%20which%20you%20are%20not%20being%20forthcoming%20about%20with%20those%20it%20impacts.%20All%20of%20these%20possibilities%20break%20the%20trust%20of%20your%20employees%20who%20have%20not%20only%20personal%20experience%20that%20shows%20the%20benefits%20of%20remote%20work%2C%20but%20have%20seen%20the%20extensive%20data%20which%20supports%20that%20experience.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cbr%3EData%20from%20independent%20research%20has%20shown%20time%20and%20time%20again%20that%20companies%20which%20embrace%20flexible%20in-office%20policies%20allow%20a%20more%20diverse%20set%20of%20workers%20to%20sustainably%20and%20effectively%20contribute%20to%20the%20shared%20goals%20of%20businesses%20like%20ours.%20If%20being%20inclusive%20and%20understanding%20of%20employees'%20personal%20working%20styles%20and%20circumstances%20isn't%20enough%20to%20justify%20why%20this%20is%20the%20right%20approach%20for%20us%20to%20take%2C%20research%20is%20clear%20that%20diverse%20perspectives%20lead%20to%20more%20innovation%2C%20productivity%2C%20and%20resilience.%20This%20diversity%20in%20backgrounds%2C%20locations%2C%20and%20working%20styles%20is%20essential%20to%20AWS'%20ability%20to%20hire%20and%20retain%20exceptional%20talent%20and%20remain%20a%20market%20leader%20and%20innovator%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cbr%3EBy%20rigidly%20mandating%20a%205-day%20in-office%20culture%20and%20telling%20employees%20who%20cannot%20or%20will%20not%20contribute%20to%20the%20company's%20mission%20in%20this%20specific%20way%20that%20%26quot%3Bthere%20are%20other%20companies%20around%2C%26quot%3B%20you%20are%20silencing%20critical%20perspectives%20and%20damaging%20our%20culture%20and%20our%20future%20in%20doing%20so.%20Moreover%2C%20this%20does%20not%20uphold%20Amazon's%20espoused%20%26quot%3BStrive%20to%20be%20Earth's%20Best%20Employer%26quot%3B%20leadership%20principle%2C%20especially%20for%20select%20and%20protected%20groups%20who%20have%20sought%20a%20safer%2C%20more%20inclusive%2C%20and%20healthier%20work%20environment%20and%20are%20disproportionately%20impacted%20by%20these%20policies.%20These%20groups%20include%20but%20are%20not%20limited%20to%20working%20parents%20(especially%20those%20with%20young%20children)%2C%20employees%20who%20are%20neurodiverse%20or%20have%20disabilities%20or%20disorders%2C%20workers%20with%20caretaking%20responsibilities%2C%20and%20workers%20on%20a%20visa%20who%20have%20no%20choice%20but%20to%20comply%20or%20risk%20having%20to%20leave%20their%20home%20by%20quitting.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cbr%3EWhile%20your%20remarks%20focus%20on%20some%20of%20the%20benefits%20you%20perceive%20in%20in-person%20collaboration%2C%20they%20fail%20to%20even%20acknowledge%20the%20significant%20challenges%20it%20presents%20to%20these%20valued%20workers%20who%20have%20often%20overcome%20adversity%20at%20every%20level%20in%20order%20to%20contribute%20to%20Amazon's%20mission.%20In%20order%20to%20highlight%20these%20challenges%2C%20we%20have%20included%20a%20selection%20of%20anonymous%20stories%20from%20Amazon%20employees%20about%20the%20impact%20Amazon's%203-day%20in-office%20policy%20has%20already%20had%20on%20their%20life%20and%20work%20with%20this%20letter.%20In%20addition%2C%20studies%20show%20that%20Return%20To%20Office%20mandates%20tend%20to%20push%20out%20more%20senior%20and%20tenured%20employees%20across%20the%20board%2C%20who%20may%20be%20best%20poised%20to%20participate%20in%20and%20give%20insight%20into%20these%20white-boarding%20and%20brainstorming%20sessions%20you%20refer%20to%2C%20while%20hurting%20the%20morale%20of%20those%20who%20stay.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cbr%3EYou%20have%20not%20addressed%20these%20issues%20nor%20presented%20any%20solution%20to%20them%20while%20touting%20the%20new%20and%20even%20more%20impactful%205-day%20policy.%20We%20do%20not%20accept%20this%20from%20our%20leaders.%20We%20see%20and%20value%20contributions%20from%20workers%20of%20these%20groups%20every%20day%2C%20and%20will%20not%20stand%20silently%20by%20while%20you%20dismiss%20their%20humanity%20and%20trivialize%20their%20impact.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cbr%3EOur%20time%20working%20remotely%20during%20the%20height%20of%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%20proved%20that%20we%20are%20effective%2C%20creative%2C%20and%20successful%20without%20being%20primarily%20in-person%2C%20and%20to%20take%20no%20lessons%20from%20that%20experience%20would%20be%20extremely%20disappointing%2C%20because%20Amazon%20is%20and%20always%20will%20be%20a%20global%20company.%20We%20will%20always%20collaborate%20with%20teams%20and%20stakeholders%20in%20different%20physical%20locations%2C%20countries%2C%20and%20timezones%20where%20the%20primary%2C%20and%20potentially%20only%2C%20interaction%20is%20virtual.%20We%20have%20tools%20and%20approaches%20to%20do%20this%20effectively%20which%20are%20not%20novel%20or%20difficult%20to%20use.%20On%20the%20contrary%2C%20pushing%20for%20more%20time%20in-office%20will%20harm%20these%20countless%20cross-regional%20interactions%20as%20there%20will%20be%20significantly%20fewer%20overlapping%20working%20hours%20between%20collaborators.%20This%20can%20lead%20to%20meetings%20that%20might%20have%20been%20done%20by%20videoconferencing%20now%20taking%20place%20via%20asynchronous%20mechanisms%20like%20email%2C%20which%20slows%20the%20velocity%20of%20decision-making%20from%20minutes%20to%20hours%20or%20days.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cbr%3EFinally%2C%20by%20taking%20this%20action%2C%20AWS%20is%20not%20living%20up%20to%20its%20full%20potential%20and%20is%20creating%20a%20bleak%20outlook%20for%20its%20future.%20While%20it%20is%20absolutely%20true%20that%20there%20are%20challenges%20with%20flexible%20and%20remote%20work%2C%20we%20have%20always%20been%20a%20company%20that%20solves%20problems%20in%20new%2C%20exciting%2C%20and%20innovative%20ways%2C%20rather%20than%20relying%20on%20antiquated%20approaches%20that%20happened%20to%20work%20well%20some%20time%20in%20the%20past.%20The%20cloud%20computing%20industry%20that%20we%20now%20base%20our%20work%20and%20livelihoods%20on%20might%20not%20exist%20today%20if%20we%20had%20adhered%20to%20that%20restrictive%20thinking%20in%20our%20early%20days.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cbr%3EGiven%20the%20scale%20of%20the%20problems%20we%20tackle%20across%20a%20workforce%20which%20is%20distributed%20all%20over%20the%20world%2C%20we%20are%20not%20content%20with%20relying%20on%20spontaneous%20in-office%20conversations%20to%20make%20progress%20and%20drive%20new%20ideas.%20We%20are%20instructed%20to%20collect%2C%20interpret%2C%20and%20act%20on%20data%20and%20invent%20new%20mechanisms%20to%20affect%20the%20outcomes%20we%20want%20to%20see%2C%20not%20to%20sit%20back%20and%20hope%20good%20things%20happen.%20We%20worry%20that%20when%20customers%20see%20us%20encounter%20a%20true%20challenge%20and%20refuse%20to%20solve%20problems%20that%20stand%20in%20the%20way%20of%20embracing%20it%2C%20they%20will%20rightly%20lose%20trust%20in%20AWS'%20ability%20to%20innovate.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cbr%3EFor%20these%20reasons%20we%20urge%20you%20to%20reconsider%20your%20comments%20and%20your%20position%20on%20the%20proposed%205-day%20in-office%20mandate.%20Remote%20and%20flexible%20work%20is%20an%20opportunity%20for%20Amazon%20to%20take%20the%20lead%2C%20not%20a%20threat.%20We%20want%20to%20work%20for%20a%20company%20and%20for%20leaders%20that%3Cbr%3Erecognize%20and%20seize%20this%20moment%20to%20challenge%20us%20to%20reinvent%20how%20we%20work.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cbr%3ERespectfully%20signed%20by%20523%20Amazonians%2C%20172%20of%20whom%20have%20elected%20to%20include%20their%20name%20below.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EEditor's%20note%3A%20BI%20has%20removed%20the%20names%20of%20the%20employees%20who%20signed%20the%20letter%20to%20protect%20their%20privacy.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EAre%20you%20a%20tech-industry%20employee%20or%20someone%20else%20with%20insight%20to%20share%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EContact%20the%20reporters%2C%20Jyoti%20Mann%20and%20Ashley%20Stewart%2C%20via%20the%20encrypted%20messaging%20app%20Signal%20at%20jyotimann.11%20or%20%2B1-425-344-8242.%20Email%20them%20at%20jmann%40businessinsider.com%20and%20astewart%40businessinsider.com.%20Use%20a%20nonwork%20device.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-employees-open-letter-aws-ceo-office-return-rto-2024-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1730308876000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F672279119b3250dbbceb35b3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22origin